{"search_data": "Central, Jammu & KashmirSahaj Bijli Har Ghar Yojana \u2013 Saubhagya Scheme launched in Jammu and KashmirDeputy CM of Jammu and Kashmir has launched this scheme.Subsequently, the state govt. will provide electricity to the poor people as identified in the Socio Economic and Caste Census data of 2011.Accordingly, govt. will provide connections at Rs 500 which poor people can pay in 10 installments in their upcoming bills.Henceforth to avail the benefits of this scheme, applicants will have to make on the spot registration. For this reason, applicants will have to furnish an identity proof.This Saubhagya initiative of the Modi\u2019s Central govt is for the empowerment of the unprivileged sections of the society.Subsequently, the state govt. will take every possible measures to ensure that the beneficiaries are identified and are receiving the benefits in a transparent manner.Furthermore, govt. will constitute several teams in consultation with the electric line departments. This is to ensure that the genuine and deserving ones will receive the electricity connections.Jammu and Kashmir state govt. is taking every possible measure to strengthen the power sector. The state govt. will adopt several other mechanisms to improve the electric infrastructure in the state. Furthermore, J&K gov. will emphasize on increasing the power generation and transmission capacity of the state to realize the dream of \u201cPower for All\u201d.References"}